        <body>
            <h1>Wake-Me-Up Omlette</h1>
            <h3>Ingredients Required</h3>
            
            <ul>
                <li>3 Eggs</li>
                <li>Hot Salsa (the hotter the better)</li>
                <li>Sharp Cheddar Cheese</li>
                <li>Crumbled Bacon</li>
            </ul>
            
            <h3>Now Put it All Together.</h3>
            
            <ol>
                <li>Scramble eggs and pour into non-stick skillet on med-high.</li>
                <li>Allow the eggs to cook on one side then flip the eggs over using a spatula (this takes some practice).</li>
                <li>Pour in cheese (to your taste).</li>
                <li>Add bacon crumbles (to your taste).</li>
                <li>Using the spatula, scoop the right half of the omlette over so it covers the cheese and bacon. </li>
                <li>Cook a few more minutes until cheese is melted.</li>
                <li>Put on a plate and pour over hot salsa then serve.</li>
            </ol>
    
        </body>
